<title>CONGO: Congo Brazzaville premier urges truce.</title>
<headline>Congo Brazzaville premier urges truce.</headline>
<dateline>BRAZZAVILLE 1997-06-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The prime minister of Congo Brazzaville called on Saturday for a truce in political and communal clashes rocking the capital and said President Pascal Lissouba would accept mediation and dialogue to end the crisis.</p>
<p>Charles David Ganao said on state radio that Lissouba had accepted a mediation offer from Gabon's veteran president, Omar Bongo, and that a broadboased consultation between the government and the political class would begin on Sunday.</p>
